## MCP prompts (underused but useful)

- `detect_impact` ÔÇö guided pre-commit analysis
- `generate_map` ÔÇö architecture doc + mermaid from the graph

## Index freshness (graph + embeddings)

- After meaningful code changes: `npm run gitnexus:refresh` (includes `--embeddings`)
- Pre-commit hook runs incremental refresh when hooks installed (`npm run hooks:install`)
- **Missing embeddings** (`stats.embeddings === 0` with symbols indexed) = stale ÔÇö `agent-refresh` rebuilds vectors
- Embeddings preserved on incremental refresh; `--drop-embeddings` only when rebuilding vectors intentionally
- If MCP says stale after refresh, restart Cursor to reload the MCP server

## MCP unreachable ÔÇö warn immediately

If GitNexus MCP fails, tell the user: _"GitNexus MCP is unreachable ÔÇö impact/detect_changes/graph queries unavailable. Falling back to Grep/Read without structural safety checks."_ Do NOT silently fall back.

## Workspace contract (non-negotiable)

- `impact` BEFORE editing any function / class / method ÔÇö report blast radius
- `detect_changes` BEFORE committing
- Warn on HIGH / CRITICAL risk before proceeding
- NEVER find-and-replace renames ÔÇö use `rename`

